w('<div class="tc"><div class="tl">Neither (Positive-Sum)</div><div class="tt">Bezos\'s wealth reflects genuine value creation: Amazon transformed retail efficiency, created millions of jobs, and delivered unprecedented consumer value. The question\'s zero-sum framing misunderstands how entrepreneurial wealth is generated in competitive markets.</div></div>\n')
w('</div>\n')
w('<div class="sh">&#128196; Essay Structure</div>\n')
w('<div class="sf">\n')
w('<div class="ss"><div class="sn" style="background:#059669;color:#fff">1</div><div class="sb"><div class="stit">Introduction</div><div class="spts">Define "at the expense of" as zero-sum. Introduce Amazon\'s scale. State your answer clearly upfront.</div></div></div>\n')
w('<div class="ss"><div class="sn" style="background:#059669;color:#fff">2</div><div class="sb"><div class="stit">Customers: Positive-Sum</div><div class="spts">Consumer surplus evidence. Competitive pricing strategy. Network effects and innovation. Verdict: NOT at customers\' expense.</div></div></div>\n')
w('<div class="ss"><div class="sn" style="background:#059669;color:#fff">3</div><div class="sb"><div class="stit">Employees: Mixed Evidence</div><div class="spts">Wage data and injury rates. Monopsony power analysis. $15 minimum wage counterargument. Verdict: Partially at employees\' expense.</div></div></div>\n')
w('<div class="ss"><div class="sn" style="background:#059669;color:#fff">4</div><div class="sb"><div class="stit">Structural Analysis</div><div class="spts">Is this about Bezos specifically or capitalism generally? Role of regulation. Could workers have captured more value?</div></div></div>\n')
w('<div class="ss"><div class="sn" style="background:#059669;color:#fff">5</div><div class="sb"><div class="stit">Conclusion</div><div class="spts">Bezos got rich primarily through value creation (not extraction from customers), but workers did bear real costs. The answer is: employees yes, customers no.</div></div></div>\n')
